				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">1) Yes, all of my donor boards are single maskROM boards<br /><br />2) Yes, the ROMs are headerless and I just load them directly.  I have tried mirroring the ROM to the upper banks just in case an open bus on the donor board was to blame, but I didn't interleave the ROM or any other trickery.<br /><br />3) The 29F032B is wired up to the maskROM pins just the way you'd expect if the rest of the circuitry was removed, everything else on the daughterboard simply connects a microcontroller to the address and data lines for in-circuit programming.  So no address re-mapping or anything of the sort.<br /><br />4) All of the donor boards I've used have had the full 36-pin footprint, so I have connected all of the pins.  I can't confirm whether or not the upper address lines are actually connected to anything on the donor board (some smaller games will leave these open bus), but I typically mirror the ROM to the upper address banks anyway (e.g. testing the SHVC-1A3M-30 board using a Zelda:LttP ROM, I just copied the ROM 4 times since it's 1MB).</div>

